// Handwritten MLIR for a transposed MXFP4 GEMM with a specialized epilogue.
//
// Shape: M=256, N=192, K=256. Inputs: MXFP4 (f4E2M1FN) with f8E8M0FNU scales.
// Output: bf16, row-major C[M, N].
//
// The kernel computes C^T = B * A^T by swapping operand roles:
//   - Weight matrix B becomes the MFMA left operand (A role).
//   - Activation matrix A becomes the MFMA right operand (B role, preshuffled).
// After the MFMAs, C^T lives in registers in transposed order.
//
// The epilogue uses amdgpu.permlane_swap to exchange data between lanes and
// reassembles C^T into contiguous C[M, N] rows. This allows wide
// vector<8xbf16> stores (buffer_store_dwordx4) instead of the scalar stores
// the compiler would otherwise emit.
//
// A and B scales are preshuffled and loaded directly from global memory into
// VGPRs, bypassing shared memory for the scale operands.
//
// Used by: examples/python/7.1_schedule.py
//          (test_dbuf_8wave_pingpong_mxfp_gemm_Bshuffle_lds_transposed)

